mall toy.)<br><br>The kids get to play with those things while mom goes in and throws the homemade sticky buns (even the carmel is homemade) into the oven to bake.  Everyone eats sticky buns and milk, then gets cleaned up and starts opening gifts. <br><br>Gifts are always passed out by one of the kids.  One gift at a time so we can all ooooh and aaaaah over each one.  After that, it all goes to hell.  Every gift that was given by a sister or cousin makes noise.  (Mom takes the battery out a couple of days later out of sheer frustration, telling the kids, &quot;Ohh, it must be broke.  I'm sorry, honey.&quot;)<br><br>Then, around 3pm or so, we all have a mexican feast.  (This was my families tradition because we were still eating turkey leftovers from Thanksgiving.)  It always includes Navajo Taco's (Taco stuff on fried bread), encheladas (sp?), and nachos.  Mmm mmm mmm! <br><br>Well, that's my Christmas.  I have come to really enjoy every last minute of these traditions.  Yes, even the waking up early.  Yes, even the noisy toys that mysteriously break a couple of days later.  Yes, even the silly PJ's.  Hehe.<br><br>To all of you:<br>Enjoy your family.  Enjoy your traditions.  Enjoy the season.  <br><br>Peace and love to everyone. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ulazarelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lazarelle</A> at: 12/24/01 2:34:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/urangergoldeneyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RangerGoldeneyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#000000>(12/24/01 5:58:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fsynchonlinefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fortunecity.com/rivendell/rhydin/79/bv8.jpg Height=200 Width=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=t